  "uuid": "efa4935ebafc6c038f6a7c8f9a6e912a",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Training Coordinator",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a proactive training team member to plan, implement, and coordinate employee training & development programs, ensuring compliance and boosting workforce efficiency. This role acts as a bridge between HR and operational departments, involving the identification of training needs, scheduling sessions, maintaining training records, and evaluating program effectiveness.</p><p>The ideal candidate will possess excellent communication, organizational, and interpersonal skills, with a passion for supporting employee growth and development.<br /></p><p><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong><br /><br />1.     Support coordination with internal stakeholders and external training providers to meet training requirements.</p><p>2.     Coordinate in-house and external training programmes, including enrolment, logistics, attendance tracking, and programme delivery.</p><p>3.     Maintain training calendars, records, completion status, certificates, evaluation forms, and ensure documentation meets audit and ISO compliance requirements.</p><p>4.     Serve as the primary point of contact for training enquiries, enrolment status, and programme coordination.</p><p>5.     Communicate course information, training schedules, reminders, and updates to employees and supervisors.</p><p>6.     Compile training materials, review e-learning content for accuracy and consistency, analyse training results, and gather feedback to identify improvement areas.</p><p>7.     Support onboarding orientation, internships, industrial attachments, educational partnerships, Training digitalisation initiatives, and various audits.<br /></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Possess Degree/Diploma in Human Resource Management or in any discipline </li><li>One (1) year of experience in HR</li><li>Fast learner, meticulous, detail oriented, able to maintain confidentiality and work independently</li><li>Proactive, able to multi-task and work in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Good knowledge of employment legislation and regulatory compliance</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office applications</li><li>Good interpersonal skills with a high level of accountability, initiative, and willingness to learn</li><li>Good team player with a positive working attitude</li></ul>",
